Red hot and delicious! 🔥 Perfect chutney for idli & dosa 🍴

Made using the @atomberg Yulia 750W Mixer Grinder, which comes with 4 multifunctional jars, including a chopper jar and coarse mode for a silbatta-like texture.

Here's a simple recipe for Idli and Dosa Tomato Onion Chutney:

🌿 Ingredients
- 1 tablespoon oil
- 1 tablespoon roasted chana dal
- 1 tablespoon urad dal
- 1/4 cup peanuts
- 3-4 dry red chilies, soaked
- 3-4 garlic cloves
- 2 tomatoes, chopped
- 1 onion, sliced
- 1 small piece of tamarind
- Salt to taste

🌿 For Tempering
- 1 teaspoon oil
- 1/2 teaspoon mustard seeds
- 1/4 teaspoon urad dal
- 1/4 teaspoon chana dal
- 1/4 teaspoon asafoetida (hing)
- 2-3 dry red chilies
- Fresh curry leaves

🌿 Instructions
1. Heat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add roasted chana dal, urad dal, peanuts, soaked dry red chilies, and garlic cloves. Sauté until fragrant.
2. Add chopped tomatoes and sliced onion. Cook until the tomatoes are soft.
3. Blend the mixture to your desired consistency, adding water as needed.
4. Prepare the tempering by heating oil and adding mustard seeds, urad dal, chana dal, asafoetida, and dry red chilies. Let it splutter.
5. Add the tempering to the chutney and mix well.

🌿 Serving
Enjoy with:

- Idli (steamed rice cake)
- Dosa (South Indian fermented crepe)
- Vada (fried lentil doughnut)

🌿 Tips
- Adjust spice levels to your taste.
- Store in an airtight container in the fridge for up to a week.
- For a thicker consistency, cook longer or add less water.

Gond Katira: the ultimate summer superfood! This natural coolant is a must-have for summer😍

🌸 What is Gond Katira?

• Gond Katira, also known as Tragacanth gum, is derived from the sap of the Astragalus plant.
• Gond Katira also known as Badam Pisin or Almond gum is obtained from almond tree.
• It is commonly found in the form of flakes or crystals that are white or light yellow in color.
• They appear as translucent solid crystals which take the form of jelly when dissolved in water.
• It has no significant odour or taste.
• Having this natural coolant daily during summer can lower the risk of heat strokes and maintain your overall health.
• It controls nose-bleeding issue that develops in children during hot summers
